title: Arizona Secretary of State Candidates Spar Over Accepting Election Results
description: Adrian Fontes, the Democratic nominee, promised to accept the outcome and called on his Republican rival, Mark Finchem, to do the same.
dc:creator: Jazmine Ulloa

media:content.media:credit: Caitlin O'Hara for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Adrian Fontes, a Democrat running for secretary of state in Arizona, in Laveen, Ariz., last week.
